            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-42496-perl-base",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-42496 critical vulnerability for perl-base package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Archive::Tar versions before 3.08 for Perl extract symlinks with attacker controlled targets outside the extraction directory.  _make_special_file() passes the tar header's linkname to symlink() without validating it against absolute paths or .. segments. The secure-extract mode check that guards regular file extraction does not cover the symlink target.  A subsequent open through the extracted name reads or writes the attacker chosen path."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42496",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-42496\nSeverity: critical\nPackage: perl-base\nVersion: 5.40.1-7+b1\nFix Version: \nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-42496](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42496)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-42496**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| critical  | perl-base  | 5.40.1-7+b1  |   | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-42496](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-42496)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/perl-base@5.40.1-7%2Bb1?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=perl%405.40.1-7"
                ],
                "security-severity": "9.1"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-8376-perl-base",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-8376 critical vulnerability for perl-base package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "Perl versions through 5.43.10 have a heap buffer overflow when compiling regular expressions with a repeated fixed string on 32-bit builds.  Perl_study_chunk in regcomp_study.c checked the size of the joined substring buffer in characters rather than bytes. For a quantified fixed substring with a large minimum count, the byte length mincount * l could overflow SSize_t, producing an undersized SvGROW allocation; the subsequent copy writes past the end of the buffer.  A caller that compiles an attacker-controlled regular expression on a 32-bit perl build triggers a heap buffer overflow at compile time."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-8376",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-8376\nSeverity: critical\nPackage: perl-base\nVersion: 5.40.1-7+b1\nFix Version: 5.40.1-8\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-8376](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-8376)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-8376**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| critical  | perl-base  | 5.40.1-7+b1  | 5.40.1-8  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-8376](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-8376)  |\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "purls": [
                  "pkg:deb/debian/perl-base@5.40.1-7%2Bb1?arch=amd64\u0026distro=debian\u0026upstream=perl%405.40.1-7"
                ],
