            {
              "id": "CVE-2026-48959-perl-base",
              "name": "DpkgMatcherExactIndirectMatch",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "CVE-2026-48959 high vulnerability for perl-base package"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "IO::Uncompress::Unzip versions before 2.220 for Perl allow CPU exhaustion via per-byte read loop in fastForward.  fastForward() compares length $offset (the digit count of the offset, 1 to 19) against the chunk size $c instead of $offset itself, so $c shrinks from 16 KiB to 1-19 bytes per iteration.  Extracting a named entry from an attacker supplied zip via IO::Uncompress::Unzip-\u003enew($zip, Name =\u003e $target) drives a per-byte read loop scaling with the entry's compressed size, up to the non-Zip64 4 GiB cap."
              },
              "helpUri": "https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-48959",
              "help": {
                "text": "Vulnerability CVE-2026-48959\nSeverity: high\nPackage: perl-base\nVersion: 5.40.1-7+b1\nFix Version: 5.40.1-8\nType: deb\nLocation: /var/lib/dpkg/status\nData Namespace: debian:distro:debian:unstable\nLink: [CVE-2026-48959](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-48959)",
                "markdown": "**Vulnerability CVE-2026-48959**\n| Severity | Package | Version | Fix Version | Type | Location | Data Namespace | Link |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| high  | perl-base  | 5.40.1-7+b1  | 5.40.1-8  | deb  | /var/lib/dpkg/status  | debian:distro:debian:unstable  | [CVE-2026-48959](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-48959)  |\n"
              },
